## Workflow Notes
This flow can be seen as a merge between git-flow and trunk based dev. 

- From git-flow perspective, release and hotfixes branches dont exist and are commited straight to master. develop branch acts the same but without the prior mentioned branches.

- From trunk based perspective, trunk is a branch named 'develop' and releases are always in master using tags. Hotfixes are done in master and optionally merged on develop, eventually develop will get the hotfix on the next sync to master anyway.

On develop, pre-releases are using feature toggles like trunk based development. Look at it like a next-release branch that gets synchronized with master on each pre-release (non beta) state.

On master, releases and hotfixes are marked with Tags, non tagged commits on master are pre-release changes.
